00:51:43,720 --> 00:51:46,220
by נזיר Nazir is טעם כעיקר, ta'am ke-ikar, that applies everywhere. You

1098
00:51:46,220 --> 00:51:48,840
have a special פסוק pasuk by חטאת, chatas, that's היתר מצטרף לאיסור,

1099
00:51:47,960 --> 00:51:50,560
heter mitztaref le-issur, which is a unique הלכה halacha by חטאת. chatas.

1100
00:51:50,560 --> 00:51:55,140
Rabbi Akiva says I already know טעם כעיקר ta'am ke-ikar from כלי

1101
00:51:55,140 --> 00:51:58,400
מדין. Klei Midyan. So, and then it says again by נזיר, Nazir,

1102
00:51:58,400 --> 00:52:00,940
that's telling you היתר מצטרף לאיסור. heter mitztaref le-issur. Why not say

1103
00:52:00,940 --> 00:52:03,920
that that applies everywhere? I would have, if that would have been

1104
00:52:03,920 --> 00:52:06,620
the only case, because then it would have applied everywhere. But the

1105
00:52:06,620 --> 00:52:09,480
fact that the Torah repeated it by קדשים, Kodshim, which it didn't

1106
00:52:09,480 --> 00:52:12,340
have to repeat it, teaches me that היתר מצטרף לאיסור heter mitztaref

1107
00:52:12,340 --> 00:52:16,220
le-issur is an exception, only to be applied by נזיר Nazir and

1108
00:52:16,220 --> 00:52:18,680
by קדשים. Kodshim. But one way or another, we know a principle

1109
00:52:18,680 --> 00:52:21,780
of טעם כעיקר ta'am ke-ikar either from כלי מדין Klei Midyan according

1110
00:52:21,780 --> 00:52:24,340
